This package is a PHP port of the Swiss bank import rules published by
Banana.ch SA:

    https://github.com/BananaAccounting/Switzerland
    Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0
    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

What was ported is the factual knowledge encoded in that work: which column
headings each bank prints, in which languages, which way its amounts are signed,
which date notations it uses, and where its quirks are. That knowledge is the
result of years of contact with real exports, and Banana.ch published it openly.

What was not taken is source code. This package is an independent implementation
with a different architecture — a shared multilingual column vocabulary and
declarative bank profiles, rather than one hand-written converter per bank — in a
different language. No file, function or fragment was copied. Every behaviour was
re-derived from the published scripts and covered by its own tests, and several
were found to differ once checked.

The acknowledgement is made because that work is where the knowledge came from,
and because attribution is owed whether or not the licence compels it here.
